               <head>Sufi treatise on divine names</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of ʿAyn al-maʿānī by ʿĪsá al-Jundī al-Sindī al-Hindī al-Birārī al-Shaṭṭārī al-Qādirī, known as ʿIshqī and entitled ʿAyn al-ʿUrafāʾ</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1018-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658573.0x000001 viaf_61432412">ʿĪsá al-Jundī al-Sindī al-Hindī al-Birārī al-Shaṭṭārī al-Qādirī, known as ʿIshqī and entitled ʿAyn al-ʿUrafāʾ</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22199">ʿAyn al-maʿānī</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on mystical-theosophical description of the talismanic and apotropaic properties of <persName key="person_f7070" role="subject">Allāh</persName>’s sacred names by <persName key="viaf_61432412" role="aut">ʿĪsá ibn Qāsim ibn Yūsuf ibn Rukn al-Dīn ibn Maʿrūf ibn Shihāb al-Dīn al-Maʿrūfī al-Shihābī al-Jundī al-Sindī al-Hindī al-Birārī al-Shaṭṭārī al-Qādirī</persName>, known as ʿIshqī and entitled ʿAyn al-ʿUrafāʾ, and completed at <placeName>Burhānpūr</placeName> in 997/1589.
                        </p>
                        <p>The treatise amplifies a shorted work, entitled <title>Rawz̤at al-ḥusná (<sic>Ḥusaynī</sic>) fī sharḥ asmāʾ Allāh al-ḥusná (<sic>Ḥusaynī</sic>
                           </title>), similar in subject and by the same author, completed in 989/1581. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Elaborate diagrams after folio 80v, although some important data has been omitted by the scribe for the sake of space. 
Incomplete ink drawing of a female bust, probably based on an Indian (Delhi?) original drawing or painting, on folio 115v. 
</p>
                        <p>Scribal nastaʿlīq, occasionally transitioning to shikastah āmīz, by multiple hands. 
</p>
                        <p>Occasional dense annotations in margins and interlinear spaces. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. </p>
                        <p>Binding damaged (combed marbled paper on pasteboards edged with brown leather; internal matter exposed in areas, including Persian letters and accounts for repairs?), labelled. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; cropped; heavily stained along upper and lower edges, fungal stains; wormholes, later repairs. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
